Third-party data attribution
============================

Scalar API Reference
--------------------

The interactive API reference page vendors the standalone build of
@scalar/api-reference:

  https://scalar.com
  https://github.com/scalar/scalar

Scalar is licensed under the MIT license; the full license text is bundled
next to the vendored build at public/vendor/scalar/LICENSE. The copy at
public/vendor/scalar/standalone.js is an unmodified upstream release build
(the version is recorded in its header comment).

caniemail
---------

The HTML client-compatibility checks in this application use the caniemail
email-client support dataset:

  https://www.caniemail.com
  https://github.com/shellscape/caniemail

The caniemail data is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International license (CC-BY-4.0): https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Modifications: the copy bundled at resources/data/caniemail/features.json is a
snapshot of the upstream dataset with the per-feature "test_results_url" fields
removed; it is otherwise unmodified. A fresh copy synced at runtime via
`php artisan htmlcheck:sync-data` is fetched from upstream unmodified.
